Class LocalVariableDetector

java.lang.Object
  org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor
      net.sourceforge.earticleast.app.LocalVariableDetector

 class LocalVariableDetector
extends org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor

This class looks for local declarations of local variables, their assignmetns and the references to them. It is an example for how to extend ASTVisitor.

Project page: http://sourceforge.net/projects/earticleast

Author:
Thomas Kuhn

visit

public boolean visit(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.VariableDeclarationStatement node)
Looks for local variable declarations. For every occurence of a local variable, a VariableBindingManager is created and stored in localVariableManagers map.

Overrides:
visit in class org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor
Parameters:
node - the node to visit
Returns:
static false to prevent that the simple name in the declaration is understood by visit(SimpleName) as reference

visit

public boolean visit(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Assignment node)
Visits Assignment AST nodes (e.g. x = 7 + 8 ). Resolves the binding of the left hand side (in the example: x). If the binding is found in the localVariableManagers map, we have an assignment of a local variable. The variable binding manager of this local variable then has to be informed about this assignment.

Overrides:
visit in class org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor
Parameters:
node - the node to visit

visit

public boolean visit(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.SimpleName node)
Visits SimpleName AST nodes. Resolves the binding of the simple name and looks for it in the localVariableManagers map. If the binding is found, this is a reference to a local variable. The variable binding manager of this local variable then has to be informed about that reference.

Overrides:
visit in class org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor
Parameters:
node - the node to visit
